import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    job_counts = data.groupby('job')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    job_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Job Title')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job titles in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['sex'])['count'].sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.bar(data['sex'], data['count'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Gender')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('How does the count of individuals vary by gender?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('year')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['count'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the trend in the number of individuals over time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['perc'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['perc'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median = {:.2f}'.format(data['perc'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Percentage')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of percentages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='perc', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 8))
    ax.bar(data['job'], data['perc'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Job Title')
    ax.set_ylabel('Percentage')
    ax.set_title('How does the percentage of individuals vary by job title?')
    ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
